#: ../../P/prepend.rst:9
msgid ""
"[by analogy with ‘append’] To prefix. As with ‘append’ (but not ‘prefix’ or "
"‘suffix’ as a verb), the direct object is always the thing being added and "
"not the original word (or character string, or whatever). \"If you prepend a"
" semicolon to the line, the translation routine will pass it through "
"unaltered.\""
msgstr ""
"[‘append’との類推による]前に付けること。‘append’と同様に(ただし動詞としての‘prefix’や‘suffix’とは違って)、直接目的語は常に追加されるものであって、元の語(や文字列など)ではない。「行の前にセミコロンをprependすれば、翻訳ルーチンはそれを変更せずに通す」"
